JD 27-
Roles and responsibilities of an HR Executive:
Recruitment and Selection:
Identifying staffing needs.
Posting job vacancies.
Reviewing resumes and conducting interviews.
Selecting and hiring candidates.
Onboarding and Orientation
Facilitating the onboarding process for new hires.
Conducting orientation sessions to familiarize new employees with company policies, procedures, and culture.
Employee Relations:
Handling employee grievances and complaints.
Mediating conflicts between employees.
Implementing disciplinary procedures when necessary.
Performance Management:
Managing performance appraisal processes.
Providing feedback to employees and managers.
Identifying training and development needs.
Training and Development:
Identifying training needs within the organization.
Developing and delivering training programs.
Compensation and Benefits:
Managing payroll processes.
Administering employee benefits programs such as health insurance etc.
HR Administration:
Maintaining employee records and databases.
Managing HR-related documentation such as contracts, policies, and procedures.
HR Analytics and Reporting:
Analyzing HR metrics such as turnover rates, retention rates, etc.
Generating reports for management on HR-related KPIs.
Using data to inform HR strategies and decision-making.
Employee Engagement:
Developing and implementing strategies to enhance employee engagement and morale.
Organizing employee events and activities.
HR Policies and Procedures:
Developing and updating HR policies and procedures in line with legal requirements and best practices.
Communicating policies and procedures to employees and ensuring compliance.
HR Technology:
Utilizing HRIS (Human Resources Information Systems) and other HR tech tools to streamline HR processes and enhance efficiency.
Overall, a HR Executive plays a crucial role in managing the human capital of an organization, ensuring that it operates smoothly and effectively.
They serve as a bridge between management and employees, addressing concerns, fostering a positive work environment, and contributing to the overall success of the organization.

